- __dict__ is a dunder attribute – class dictionaries cls.__dict__ is a dictionary containing the classes methods, attribues, and descriptors
- object, instance, type and super are all special built in python classes
    - OBJECT: – the root class, every class inhertirs from it, so every value in python is an instance of object – used to create in memory instances of classes
        - object is always last in the MRO
        - accepts no arguments, returns featureless instance with no instance attributes
    - TYPE: - default metaclass, every class is an instance of type, including itself
        - type(obj) calls type w/ argument obj
        - type(name, bases, dict) creates a new class
        - calling "class cls_name(args):" calls behind the scenes type(name, bases, dict) and creates a new class
    - SUPER: – 
-  is a special class, always last in the MRO, accepts 
